The paper discusses the task of aggregating beliefs of multiple experts represented as probability distributions, which is a common problem in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed framework involves Bayesian networks, which is a popular tool in probabilistic graphical models and inference (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the accuracy of the aggregation mechanism, which is related to the evaluation of machine learning models (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT).
